HEADWORD: Sighted
<hw>Sight"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having sight, or seeing, in a
particular manner; -- used in composition; <as>as,
long-<ex>sighted</ex>, short-<ex>sighted</ex>, quick-<ex>sighted</ex>,
sharp-<ex>sighted</ex>, and the like</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

